text:
I have been coping with forging my own path. I quit my toxic job and abusive work place back in Dec and have been nose-deep in finding my voice again healing my traumas of all my past bosses and working on building myself back up from falling again. 

Everyday I show up, make art send my spark of light into the world yet bills are piling up, taxes are coming and I‚Äôm still unable yet grateful my parents let me someone in their late 30s live with them so my precious dog and self have food in my belly and a roof over my head. I truly want to help pay for some of these bills I have let slide and continue to peruse my path and purpose on this earth of transmuting darkness (healing the collective shadow self) into light. 

I get it we all have struggles and our own baggage to deal with and everything we do to help uplift and support each other is truly a blessing and inspiration to keep paying it forward.

https://warpcast.com/jacque/0x36686bef https://warpcast.com/jacque/0x16d69aee

cast.text:
I‚Äôm grateful for my mom who appeased me by going on a late walk since my dog was seizing up and I cannot afford vet bills if anything happened ATM. Listened to me and let me cry over the fact my dog cannot tell me what's wrong. 

We were sitting while I was making art and all the sudden she tensed up. I brought her and sat down with her on the ground her paw unable to touch the floor her muscles tightening. 

She is my everything ATM and is getting old ü•π thankfully the walk was good and soon to sleep.
